# ASU Desi Hub — Project Rules

## Project Context
A Next.js 16 web app for Indian international students at Arizona State University (ASU).

The product has TWO primary pillars (treat both as core, not one as secondary):

PILLAR 1 — APARTMENT DIRECTORY
A directory of apartment complexes near ASU, with:
- Real resident-submitted photos (not stock photos from leasing offices)
- Honest reviews of management (maintenance response, deposit returns, hidden fees, etc.)
- Quick facts (rent, distance to campus, sublease policy, parking, etc.)
- Indian student community signal (how many residents self-report as Indian students)

PILLAR 2 — SUBLEASE BOARD
Structured sublease listings tied to specific apartments in the directory.
- Filterable by gender, dates, rent, room type, household diet
- Listings come from a curated WhatsApp group, posted manually by admin at first,
  then auto-parsed from group messages via Twilio WhatsApp API later

ADD-ONS (build after pillars are working)
- Move-out sales (Indian students selling furniture/kitchen/electronics before leaving)
- Roommate requests
- Static guide pages: transit, food, free events, weekend trips, student survival

Target user: Indian student either (a) in India researching apartments before arrival,
or (b) current ASU student looking for housing or info.

## Tech Stack (do not deviate without asking)
- Next.js 16 (App Router)
- React 19
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS v4
- Supabase (Postgres + Auth + Storage for photos)
- MDX for static guide pages
- shadcn/ui for components
- lucide-react for icons
- next-themes for dark mode
- Deployed on Vercel

## Code Style
- Server Components by default. 'use client' only when needed (forms, filters, interactivity).
- Functional components with TypeScript interfaces for props.
- Tailwind utilities only — no inline styles, no CSS modules.
- File naming: kebab-case for files, PascalCase for components.
- Co-locate route-specific components inside the route folder.
- Shared components → /components, shared utilities → /lib.
- Always handle loading and error states for async ops.
- Use Server Actions for mutations where possible.

## Design Principles
- Mobile-first. Most users browse on phones.
- Clean and fast — inspired by https://budgetsf.vercel.app.
- Tone: direct, practical, desi-friendly. Mention dal, veg households, home states naturally.
- Dark mode from day one.
- Accessibility: semantic HTML, alt text, keyboard nav.
- Photos are first-class — the apartment directory lives or dies on photo quality.

## Database Schema (Supabase)

### apartments
- id (uuid, pk)
- name (text) — e.g. "The Local Tempe"
- slug (text, unique) — e.g. "the-local-tempe"
- address (text)
- latitude, longitude (float, nullable)
- distance_to_campus_minutes_walk (int)
- distance_to_campus_minutes_orbit (int, nullable)
- rent_min, rent_max (int)
- utilities_typically_included (boolean)
- parking_cost_monthly (int, nullable)
- sublease_allowed (enum: 'yes', 'no', 'with_approval', 'unknown')
- pet_policy (text, nullable)
- official_website (text, nullable)
- description (text, markdown supported)
- cover_photo_id (uuid, nullable, fk → apartment_photos.id)
- created_at, updated_at (timestamp)

### apartment_photos
- id (uuid, pk)
- apartment_id (uuid, fk → apartments.id)
- storage_path (text) — Supabase Storage path
- category (enum: 'bedroom', 'kitchen', 'bathroom', 'living', 'gym', 'pool', 'parking', 'exterior', 'hallway', 'other')
- caption (text, nullable)
- submitted_by_email (text)
- verified (boolean, default false)
- created_at (timestamp)

### apartment_reviews
- id (uuid, pk)
- apartment_id (uuid, fk → apartments.id)
- rating_overall (int 1-5)
- rating_maintenance (int 1-5)
- rating_management (int 1-5)
- rating_value (int 1-5)
- rating_safety (int 1-5)
- lease_term_start (date)
- lease_term_end (date)
- review_text (text)
- pros (text, nullable)
- cons (text, nullable)
- would_recommend (boolean)
- submitted_by_email (text)
- verified (boolean, default false)
- created_at (timestamp)

### subleases
- id (uuid, pk)
- apartment_id (uuid, nullable, fk → apartments.id)
- custom_apartment_name (text, nullable) — for apartments not in directory
- rent_monthly (int)
- utilities_included (boolean)
- available_from (date)
- available_until (date)
- gender_preference (enum: 'male', 'female', 'any')
- room_type (enum: 'private', 'shared')
- household_diet (enum: 'veg', 'non_veg', 'any')
- contact_method (text) — phone, email, or instagram
- additional_info (text, nullable)
- submitted_by_email (text)
- verified (boolean, default false)
- status (enum: 'active', 'taken', 'expired')
- expires_at (timestamp) — defaults to created_at + 30 days
- created_at (timestamp)

## Routes (priority order)
1. / — Landing page (featured apartments + recent subleases)
2. /apartments — Apartment directory grid with filters
3. /apartments/[slug] — Individual apartment page with photos, reviews, live subleases
4. /subleases — Sublease board with filters
5. /subleases/[id] — Individual sublease detail page
6. /submit/photo — Submit a photo to an apartment
7. /submit/review — Submit a review for an apartment
8. /submit/sublease — Submit a sublease listing
9. /admin — Admin panel (gated by my email) to verify submissions and manage apartments
10. (later) /moveout, /roommates, /transit, /food, /free, /attractions, /student

## Out of Scope (do not build)
- Payment processing, escrow, anything that holds money
- Full user auth — use email-link verification only on submissions
- WhatsApp scraping of any kind
- Mobile app
- Mentioning specific apartment staff members by name in reviews (legal risk — strip on submission)

## When in Doubt
- Ask before adding new dependencies
- Ask before changing the schema
- Prefer simple solutions over clever ones
- Photos and reviews are the moat — invest in making submission frictionless